1. d4 e6 2. Nf3 f5 3. g3 Nf6 4. Bg2 g6 5. O-O Bg7 6. c4 O-O 7. Nc3 d6 8. b3 Nc6 9. Bb2 e5 10. dxe5 dxe5 11. e4 { This offers Black a choice. } 11... Qxd1 $5 { Not really giving up the control of the d-file. In fact, Black forces one of the enemy roks to occupy the vulnerable d1-square. } ( 11... Nxe4 $5 12. Nxe4 fxe4 13. Nd2 e3 ( 13... Nd4 14. Nxe4 Bf5 $11 ) 14. fxe3 Rxf1+ 15. Nxf1 Be6 16. Qe2 { Choroszej,A (1949) -Borowy,C (1884) Warsaw YMCA Autumn-A 161st 2015 (3) 1/2-1/2 } 16... a5 $5 { One of the good moves. } 17. a3 a4 ( 17... h5 $11 ) ( 17... Qe7 18. Nd2 e4 { Now and in the main line, Black fights against the blockade on e4 and clears the e5- square for his knight. } 19. Nxe4 Ne5 20. Bd4 Bg4 21. Qb2 Bf3 22. Rf1 Nd3 23. Qc2 Bxe4 24. Bxe4 Qxe4 25. Rf4 Qe7 26. Qxd3 Bxd4 27. exd4 Qxa3 $11 ) 18. b4 e4 $5 { The same idea as above. } 19. Bxg7 Kxg7 20. Qb2+ Qf6 21. Qxf6+ Kxf6 22. Nd2 Ne5 23. Nxe4+ Ke7 24. Nc5 ( 24. c5 Rd8 ) ( 24. Rd1 Nxc4 25. Nc5 Bc8 26. Rd3 c6 $11 ) 24... Rd8 25. Nxe6 Kxe6 26. Bxb7 Rd2 27. Bd5+ Kd6 $44 ) 12. Raxd1 fxe4 ( 12... Nxe4 13. Nxe4 fxe4 { may transpose after } 14. Ng5 Nd4 15. Nxe4 Bg4 ) 13. Ng5 Bg4 14. Rde1 Nd4 15. Ncxe4 ( 15. Ngxe4 Nxe4 16. Rxe4 Bf5 17. Re3 Nc2 ( 17... c6 $11 ) 18. Bxb7 Nxe3 19. fxe3 Bh3 20. Re1 Rad8 21. Ne4 h6 22. Ba3 $44 { Edvardsson-Grabarczyk, Panormo 2001 /CBM 084 ext } ) 15... Nxe4 16. Nxe4 ( 16. Bxe4 c6 $11 { In spite of his stability on light squares, White cannot prove an obvious plan of increasing his pressure. In fact, in the game, it will be Black who will make progress on the queen side. } 17. f3 Bd7 18. Kg2 Rad8 19. h4 { Raetsky,A (2408) -Malaniuk,V (2525) Seefeld op 10th 1999 (6) 0-1 } 19... h6 20. Nh3 Bf5 21. Nf2 h5 $11 ) ( 16. Rxe4 Bf5 17. Rh4 c6 18. Nxh7 Rfe8 $44 { planning such moves as Bd3, Nf5, and showing that the white daring pieces are hanging. } 19. Ng5 $2 Bf6 $1 20. f4 exf4 $17 21. gxf4 $2 Ne2+ $19 ) 16... Rad8 17. h3 ( 17. Bxd4 $2 exd4 18. h3 Bf5 19. g4 Bxe4 20. Bxe4 d3 21. Rd1 d2 22. Bxb7 Rfe8 $17 { Mirzoev,E (2455) -Polivanov,A (2411) UKR-ch sf Omelnyk 2019 (4) 1/2-1/2 } ) 17... Bf5 18. Rb1 a5 19. Kh2 b6 20. Ba3 Rfe8 21. g4 Bc8 22. Nc3 c6 23. Bc1 Be6 ( 23... Rf8 $5 { overdefending f6 in view of Bg5 followed by Ne4. } 24. Ne4 ( 24. Bg5 Bf6 25. Be3 h5 ) 24... h5 25. Bg5 ( 25. gxh5 gxh5 26. Bg5 Rd7 $11 ) 25... hxg4 $5 ( 25... Rd7 $11 ) 26. Bxd8 Rxd8 27. hxg4 Bxg4 $44 ) ( 23... h5 $11 ) 24. Bg5 Rd7 25. Na4 ( 25. Ne4 Rf8 26. Be3 h6 ) 25... Rb8 26. Be3 { Ruban,V (2575) -Knezevic,M (2390) Anapa 1991 1/2-1/2 } 26... h5 $11 *
