1. d4 e6 2. g3 f5 3. Bg2 Nf6 4. Nf3 g6 5. O-O Bg7 6. c4 O-O 7. Nc3 d6 8. Qc2 Nc6 9. e4 { This may seem a logical consequence of the previous move, but Black is well prepared to react in the centre. } 9... e5 $1 10. dxe5 ( 10. d5 Nd4 11. Nxd4 exd4 12. Ne2 Nxe4 13. Rd1 ( 13. Bxe4 fxe4 14. Qxe4 Bf5 $19 { Gombocz, F (2188) -Papasimakopoulos, A (2248) Titled Tuesday intern op 19th Oct blitz 2021 (9) 1/2-1/2 } ) 13... Bd7 14. Nxd4 Qe7 15. Be3 Rae8 $11 ) 10... dxe5 11. Rd1 ( 11. exf5 Bxf5 ( 11... Nd4 12. Nxd4 exd4 13. Nd5 Bxf5 $11 ) ( 11... e4 12. Nxe4 Nxe4 13. Qxe4 Bxf5 $44 ) 12. Qb3 { Batsiashvili,N (2457) -Polivanov,A (2452) FRA-ch Blitz Online Qual 2020 (11) 0-1 } 12... e4 13. Ng5 ( 13. Nh4 Nd4 14. Qxb7 Be6 $13 ) 13... Nd4 14. Qxb7 Nc2 15. Rb1 Rb8 16. Qxa7 h6 17. Ngxe4 Nxe4 18. Nxe4 Re8 19. Nc5 Nd4 20. Ra1 c6 $44 { Black does not have to play for a draw by repetition. His hyperactive position and the exposed white queen yield him enough compensation for the three pawns. } ) ( 11. Bg5 h6 12. Rad1 Qe8 13. Bxf6 Rxf6 14. Nd5 Rf7 { [%cal Gf5f4] } 15. exf5 Bxf5 16. Qc1 Bg4 $15 { Yakimova, M (2198) -Lach, A (2198) Wch Blitz (Women) 2021 (7) 0-1 } ) 11... Qe8 12. Nd5 { This requires some accuracy. } 12... fxe4 $14 { This leads to a typical structure where the possibility of invading d4 compensates for the weakness of the e5-pawn. } ( 12... Rf7 $2 13. Ng5 Rd7 14. exf5 Nd4 15. Rxd4 exd4 16. Bf4 ( 16. Bd2 $18 { with the point } 16... c6 17. Re1 ) 16... c6 17. Nxf6+ Bxf6 { Magalashvili, D (2456) -Rozman, L (2343) Titled Tuesday intern op 7th July blitz 2020 (7) 1-0 } 18. Ne4 $16 ) 13. Nxf6+ ( 13. Ng5 Nd4 $15 ) ( 13. Nxc7 $2 Qf7 14. Nxa8 exf3 15. Bxf3 Nd4 $19 ) 13... Rxf6 $5 { Maintaining the possibility of putting the knight on f3 under pressure with ...Bg4. } ( { The more natural } 13... Bxf6 { is also good. } 14. Qxe4 Bf5 15. Qd5+ Kg7 16. Be3 Rd8 17. Qb5 e4 18. Rxd8 Qxd8 19. Nh4 Bc8 20. Bxe4 Nd4 $44 ) 14. Ng5 ( 14. Qxe4 Bf5 15. Qd5+ Kh8 16. Bg5 Rf7 $11 17. Qb5 $2 Bg4 $17 ) 14... Bf5 15. Qb3 ( { In the event of } 15. Nxe4 { , there is nothing wrong with retreating to f7 or f8, but Black can also play } 15... Nd4 16. Nxf6+ Bxf6 17. Qd2 Rd8 $44 { The white queen does not have good squares and White's development is incomplete. } ) 15... Rb8 16. Nxe4 Rf8 $11 *
