for returning with the knight into play. } 10... d5 11. h4 { Socko,M (2175) -Lewandowska,K (2120) POL-ch (Women) 1992 (7) 0-1 } ( 11. Nh3 Nc6 12. e3 { Polczyk,M (2132) -Pacan Milej,K (2333) POL-ch U18 Szklarska Poreba 2020 (5) 0-1 } 12... a5 $5 13. Bd2 Ne7 { [%cal Ge7f5,Gc7c6] followed by ...c7-c6 and ...Nf5. } ) 11... Nc6 12. Be3 ( 12. e3 Bf6 13. Nh3 Bxh4 $1 14. gxh4 Qxh4 $17 { [%cal Ge6e5] } 15. Nf4 $2 g5 16. Qh5 Rxf4 $19 ) 12... Ne7 13. Nh3 Nf5 14. Bg5 Bf6 $11 ) 10... d5 { Now and in other similar situations, the move ...e7-e6 proves useful. } 11. e3 c5 $1 { Black uses his freer development to challenge White in the centre. } 12. Nb3 ( 12. dxc5 Nd7 $15 13. Nb3 $6 Ne5 14. cxd5 exd5 $17 15. h3 $6 g5 $19 { [%cal Gg5g4] } ) 12... cxd4 ( 12... b6 $5 13. cxd5 exd5 14. dxc5 Nc6 $44 15. cxb6 Ne5 $15 ) 13. Nxd4 Nc6 14. Nxc6 bxc6 { Black has more space, but White's position is very solid. Black's main concern is avoiding White's counterplay. } 15. Rb1 Rb8 { Taking measures against White's queenside expansion. } ( 15... e5 16. b3 ( 16. b4 $1 a6 17. a4 $14 ) 16... Be6 17. Ba3 Rf7 18. Qe2 Qd7 19. Rbc1 Bg4 20. Qd2 Bf3 21. cxd5 cxd5 22. Rc2 Rd8 ( 22... h5 $40 ) 23. Rec1 d4 $15 24. Bf1 d3 $19 { Vakhidov, J (2500) -Wall, T (2236) Hastings Masters op 93rd 2017 (1) 1-0 } ) 16. Qa4 ( 16. b4 Qe7 17. Qc2 Rxb4 $1 18. Ba3 Rxb1 19. Bxe7 Rxe1+ 20. Bf1 Rf7 21. Bb4 Ra1 $13 ) 16... c5 $5 17. Qxa7 Qd6 $44 { [%cal Gf8f7,Gc8a6] followed by ... Ba6. } *
