1. d4 e6 2. g3 f5 3. Bg2 Nf6 4. Nh3 Be7 5. O-O O-O 6. c4 d6 7. b3 c6 8. Bb2 Qc7 9. Nd2 e5 10. Qc2 a5 $14 { This would be the perfect move if it would not delay the development for one more move. White is likely to get an optically dangerous attack, but Black has enough defensive resources. } 11. e4 { There is no other plan left. } ( 11. a3 Na6 $11 ) 11... Nxe4 12. Nxe4 fxe4 13. dxe5 dxe5 14. Rae1 { Bringing all the resources into play. } ( 14. Qxe4 { allows Black to complete his development very actively, at the cost of just one pawn. } 14... Bf5 15. Qxe5 Qxe5 16. Bxe5 Na6 17. Nf4 g5 18. Nh5 Nb4 $44 19. a3 $2 Nd3 $44 { Black's hyperactivity and White's weaknesses ensure Black enough compensation for the pawn. } ) 14... Na6 15. Bxe4 $1 { Now is when White's attack starts. } 15... Bxh3 { A piece is a piece. } 16. Bxh7+ Kh8 17. Rxe5 ( 17. Bg6 { is best met with } 17... Qd6 18. Rxe5 Bxf1 19. Kxf1 Nb4 20. Qe4 Qd3+ 21. Qxd3 Nxd3 22. Bxd3 Bf6 23. Rh5+ Kg8 24. Bc1 { White has enough compensation for the exchange, but not more than that. } 24... a4 { A familiar move, weakening White's queenside and creating a dangerous candidate for the promotion deep in the endgame. } 25. b4 Kf7 $13 ) 17... Bf6 18. Rh5 Bg4 19. Qg6 $1 { There is no way back. White has to go "all in". } 19... Qd7 20. h3 $1 ( 20. Ba3 Qe6 21. Bxf8 Rxf8 22. h3 Bxh5 23. Qxh5 Bg5 24. Bb1+ Bh6 25. Qxa5 Qxh3 $15 ) 20... Bxh5 21. Qxh5 g6 $1 22. Bxg6+ Kg8 23. Bf5 Qe7 { White has good compensation for the rook. However, the position seems to be objectively equal. } 24. Rd1 ( 24. Bxf6 Rxf6 $19 ) ( 24. Bc1 Nc5 25. Bh6 Rf7 26. Bg6 Rg7 27. Bxg7 Kxg7 28. Kg2 Rh8 29. Qg4 Rd8 $11 ) 24... Bxb2 25. Rd7 Qxd7 26. Bxd7 Nc7 $11 { White can force a perpetual at any time, but if he plays on, Black will soon get enough counterplay. Here are two possible lines. } 27. h4 ( 27. Kg2 Bg7 28. f4 Rf7 29. Bf5 Bd4 30. Bg6 Re7 31. Qg5 Kf8 32. f5 Ne8 $15 ) 27... Rf7 28. Bc8 b6 29. Qg5+ Bg7 30. Qd8+ Rf8 31. Qxc7 Raxc8 32. Qxb6 c5 33. f4 Bd4+ 34. Kg2 Rce8 35. Qxa5 Re3 36. b4 Kh7 37. Qa7+ Kh8 38. Qb6 Rf7 { Preparing to attack g3. } ( 38... Rg8 $4 39. Qh6# ) 39. bxc5 Rg7 40. Qd8+ Kh7 41. Qxd4 Rgxg3+ { with a draw by perpetual. } *
