1. d4 e6 2. Nf3 f5 { We will now examine a series of alternatives to 3.g3. } 3. h3 { Preparing a positional attack with g2-g4, as an attempt to punish Black for delaying the king's knight development. } ( 3. g4 $6 { is premature. } 3... fxg4 4. Ne5 Qh4 5. Rg1 Nf6 $15 ) ( 3. d5 { is more of a blow in the wind. } 3... Nf6 4. dxe6 ( 4. c4 Bb4+ 5. Bd2 Qe7 6. Nc3 e5 7. a3 Bxc3 8. Bxc3 d6 9. b4 O-O 10. e3 Nbd7 11. Be2 Ne4 12. Bb2 { Maistrovsky, M-Kharitonov,O Moscow Alekhine op 1996 (1) 0-1 } 12... Rf6 $13 ) 4... d5 $5 ( 4... dxe6 5. Qxd8+ Kxd8 6. Ne5 Ke8 7. g3 Bd6 8. Nc4 Bd7 9. Bg2 Bc6 10. f3 Nbd7 11. Nxd6+ cxd6 12. c4 a5 13. O-O Ke7 14. Rd1 Rhc8 $11 ) 5. Bf4 ( 5. Ng5 Qe7 6. Nc3 Bxe6 ) 5... Bd6 6. e3 Bxe6 $11 ) ( 3. Nc3 { is examined in Line 27. } ) ( { For } 3. Bg5 { see Lines 28 to 30. } ) ( 3. Bf4 { is investigated in Lines 31 to 33. } ) 3... Nf6 4. g4 d5 { An attack on the wing is answered with the consolidation of the centre. It makes no sense to waste time and clear attacking space for White by accepting the sacrifice. } 5. Rg1 ( 5. gxf5 exf5 { is likely to transpose. } ) 5... Ne4 6. Bf4 ( 6. c4 c5 { shows that White is not so well prepared for the fight in the centre, since he has wasted a few tempi on the kingside. } ) ( { Against } 6. gxf5 exf5 7. Bf4 { , Black can react in the same way as in the main line. } 7... Bd6 $14 ( 7... Nd7 8. e3 $14 ) 8. Bxd6 ( 8. e3 Bxf4 9. exf4 O-O $15 { The control over e5 cannot fully compensate for the delay in development and the weakness on f4. } ) 8... Qxd6 9. Rxg7 Nc6 10. e3 Bd7 { White has won a pawn, but fallen behind in development. } 11. c4 $5 dxc4 12. Bxc4 O-O-O 13. Nc3 Rhe8 14. Qe2 Qh6 15. Rg1 f4 { White has to react energetically. } 16. Nxe4 Rxe4 17. Bd5 Ree8 18. Bxc6 Bxc6 19. Ne5 Bd5 20. Qg4+ Kb8 21. Qxf4 Qb6 22. O-O-O Bxa2 $44 ) 6... Bd6 $14 7. Bxd6 cxd6 $5 ( 7... Qxd6 { is also possible, of course. } ) 8. gxf5 O-O $1 { A different way of sacrificing the pawn. } 9. fxe6 Bxe6 10. Qd3 Nc6 11. Nbd2 Rc8 12. c3 Qb6 $44 13. Nxe4 dxe4 14. Qd2 exf3 ( 14... Ne7 $5 15. Ng5 Bf5 16. h4 Kh8 17. Bh3 d5 18. O-O-O h6 19. Bxf5 Nxf5 20. Nh3 Nxh4 21. Rg4 Nf5 22. Rdg1 Rf6 $13 ) 15. Qh6 Rf7 16. Rxg7+ Rxg7 17. Qxe6+ Kh8 18. Qxc8+ Rg8 19. Qf5 fxe2 20. Bxe2 Qxb2 21. Qf6+ Rg7 22. Qf8+ Rg8 $11 *
