1. d4 e6 2. Nf3 f5 3. Nc3 { As clumsy as it may seem, the early development of the knight in front of the c-pawn should not be neglected in all sorts of Dutch systems. White partly gives up his territorial ambitions and goes for quick development. The main idea is territorial, though, since he plans to open the centre with e2-e4. } 3... Nf6 4. Bg5 { The most consequent continuation, threatening e2-e4 already. } ( { Preventing ...Bb4 with } 4. a3 { is too slow, of course. Black can switch to simple means: } 4... Be7 5. Bg5 Ne4 $14 ) ( 4. Qd3 { may be answered in the same way as in the main line. } 4... Bb4 ( { The early queen's commitment entirely justifies } 4... d5 { Actually, this is the simplest, but I also wanted to offer a hyper-modern solution. } 5. Bf4 c5 6. dxc5 Bxc5 7. Nb5 Na6 $11 ) 5. a3 Bxc3+ 6. Qxc3 Ne4 7. Qd3 O-O 8. Bf4 c5 9. e3 Nc6 { The structure is a bit unusual, but Black's excellent development ensures him good play. } 10. Ne5 ( 10. d5 Ne7 11. dxe6 d5 $11 ) ( 10. Be2 g5 $5 11. Bg3 d5 $13 12. c3 c4 13. Qc2 Qe7 { with considerable space advantage. } ) 10... cxd4 11. Nxc6 bxc6 12. exd4 Qb6 13. b3 ( 13. Rb1 { gives up the right to castle long in case of emergency, allowing } 13... e5 $1 14. Bxe5 Re8 15. f3 d6 16. fxe4 dxe5 $36 ) 13... Ba6 $3 { A beautiful and effective way of completing the development. } 14. Qe3 ( 14. Qxa6 Qxd4 $19 ) ( 14. c4 e5 15. Bxe5 Rae8 $15 ) 14... Bxf1 15. Rxf1 Qa5+ 16. b4 Qd5 17. f3 Nd6 18. Bxd6 Qxd6 $11 ) 4... Bb4 5. Qd3 ( 5. Qd2 { puts White under a double pin, requiring him to spend a tempo on a2-a3 later. } 5... d6 { Preparing . ..Nbd7 followed by ...h7-h6, when the reserve knight would be ready to replace its colleague in case of Bxf6. } 6. a3 ( 6. O-O-O Nbd7 7. Qe3 Qe7 8. Nb5 Ba5 9. Qa3 Bb6 10. e3 h6 11. Bh4 g5 12. Bg3 Ne4 $11 ) 6... Bxc3 7. Qxc3 Nbd7 8. e3 O-O ( { Actually, it makes sense to chase the bishop before getting castled. The king could go to the other wing, too. } 8... h6 9. Bh4 g5 10. Bg3 Nb6 11. O-O-O Bd7 12. Qa5 Bc6 13. c4 Qe7 14. Nd2 Nh5 15. f3 Nxg3 16. hxg3 a6 17. Nb3 g4 $13 18. fxg4 Qg5 $1 ) 9. Bd3 h6 10. Bh4 b6 11. Qc4 { Causing some micro problems. } 11... Kh8 $1 12. Qxe6 ( 12. O-O-O a5 13. Rhg1 Rb8 14. a4 g5 15. Bg3 Nd5 16. h4 g4 17. Nd2 N7f6 $13 ) 12... g5 ( 12... Nc5 13. Bxf6 Rxf6 14. Qa2 Nxd3+ 15. cxd3 Bb7 $44 ) 13. Qc4 { Putting c7 under pressure again, in order to restrict the enemy queen's mobility. } ( 13. Bg3 Nc5 14. Qa2 Nxd3+ 15. cxd3 Bb7 $17 ) ( 13. Qb3 gxh4 14. Nxh4 Qe8 15. Bxf5 Rg8 16. O-O-O Nf8 $13 ) 13... b5 $5 { This forces the queen to make up its mind. } ( 13... gxh4 14. Nxh4 Rg8 15. Nxf5 Nf8 $6 16. Nxh6 $16 { Jetzl,J (2213) -Williams, S (2461) London Classic op 5th 2013 (2) 1-0 } ) 14. Qxb5 ( 14. Qb3 c5 $5 ) ( 14. Qa2 gxh4 15. Nxh4 Qe8 $17 ) ( 14. Qc6 { allows Black to gain a few tempi for his development. } 14... Nb6 15. Bg3 f4 $5 16. exf4 Bd7 17. Qc3 Nfd5 18. Qd2 gxf4 { The threat ...fxg4 is not real yet, but it could soon be such, and the bishop is passive on g3 anyway. } 19. b3 Qf6 $13 ) 14... Rb8 15. Qa5 { Otherwise the queen would be later exposed to ...Nb6 } 15... gxh4 16. Nxh4 c5 $1 17. Qxd8 Rxd8 18. Nxf5 cxd4 19. exd4 Nb6 $13 ) ( 5. g4 { can be met in different ways. } 5... fxg4 ( 5... h6 6. Bxf6 Qxf6 7. gxf5 Bxc3+ 8. bxc3 exf5 9. h4 Nc6 10. e3 d6 11. h5 Be6 12. Nh4 Ne7 $11 ) 6. Ne5 Be7 7. Rg1 d6 8. Nxg4 Nxg4 9. Bxe7 Qxe7 10. Rxg4 Nd7 11. Qd3 Nf6 12. Rg3 Bd7 $11 ) ( 5. a3 { is not very inspiring. } 5... Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 b6 7. e3 Bb7 8. Bd3 d6 9. O-O Nbd7 10. Re1 h6 11. Bxf6 Nxf6 12. Nd2 O-O 13. e4 fxe4 14. Nxe4 Nxe4 ( 14... Nd5 15. g3 e5 16. dxe5 dxe5 17. Qh5 Qe8 $11 ) 15. Bxe4 Bxe4 16. Rxe4 Qd7 17. Qe2 Rae8 18. Re1 Rf6 $11 ) 5... b6 $1 { White prepares to unpin his knight, so Black should  hurry to use the enemy queen's exposure. } ( 5... d6 $6 6. O-O-O Nbd7 $6 7. e4 Bxc3 8. exf5 $18 ) ( { In a recent game, I carelessly played } 5... h6 $6 6. Bxf6 Qxf6 7. a3 Bxc3+ 8. Qxc3 Nc6 9. Ne5 $1 O-O 10. Nxc6 bxc6 11. e3 a5 12. a4 $14 { Rodriguez Ferraz,B (2057) -Marin,M (2436) I ACTIVO INTERNACIONAL DE AJEDREZ SAN CR 2023 (9) 1/2-1/2 } ) 6. a3 ( 6. O-O-O Ba6 7. Qe3 O-O 8. Ne5 Bxc3 9. Qxc3 Ne4 10. Bxd8 Nxc3 11. bxc3 Rxd8 $11 ) 6... Ba6 7. Qd2 Bxc3 8. Qxc3 Nc6 { Continuing to develop, without wasting time on getting castled. } ( 8... O-O $6 9. g4 $5 fxg4 10. Ne5 Nc6 11. Bg2 Ne7 12. Bxf6 Rxf6 13. Nxg4 Rg6 14. Bf3 Rb8 15. O-O-O $14 ) 9. d5 ( 9. Ne5 $14 Nxe5 $1 10. dxe5 Ne4 $1 11. Bxd8 Nxc3 12. Bxc7 Rc8 13. Bd6 ( 13. Bxb6 axb6 14. bxc3 Rxc3 15. Kd2 Rc5 16. f4 Ke7 17. e3 Bxf1 18. Rhxf1 Rhc8 19. Ra2 Rd5+ 20. Ke2 g5 $44 ) 13... Ne4 14. c3 Nxd6 ( 14... Rc6 15. Bb4 $16 ) 15. exd6 e5 16. O-O-O Kf7 17. e3 Bxf1 18. Rhxf1 Ke6 19. Rd2 g5 { White's extra pawn does not make itself felt in any way. } 20. f4 Rc4 21. Rf3 h5 $11 ) ( 9. g3 O-O 10. Bg2 Ne7 11. Bxf6 Rxf6 12. Ne5 Rb8 $11 ) ( 9. e3 Bxf1 10. Rxf1 O-O $11 ) 9... exd5 10. Bxf6 ( 10. O-O-O O-O 11. Bxf6 Qxf6 12. Qxf6 Rxf6 13. Rxd5 d6 $11 ) 10... Qxf6 11. Qxf6 gxf6 12. O-O-O Ne7 13. g3 O-O-O $13 { Dowgird,F (2348) -Osmonbekov,T (2136) Titled Tuesday intern op 27th July blitz 2021 (1) 1-0 } *
