1. d4 e6 2. Nf3 f5 3. Bg5 { With the knight on g8, this is a blow in the wind. } 3... Be7 $1 { Forcing White to take a decision. } 4. Bxe7 ( 4. h4 { is examined in the next lines. } ) 4... Qxe7 { This looks similar with a Bogo Indian setup, with the significant difference that here it was White who spent tempo on exchanging the bishops. } 5. Nbd2 ( 5. c4 Nf6 6. Nc3 O-O 7. e3 b6 8. Be2 Bb7 9. O-O d6 ( 9... c5 10. Qc2 Nc6 $11 ) 10. Qc2 Ne4 11. Rad1 Nd7 12. d5 Nxc3 13. Qxc3 e5 14. b4 g5 15. Nd2 a5 $14 ( 15... Rf6 16. e4 f4 { Heuser,P (2108) -Keusch,H (1953) Berlin Lichtenberger op 9th 2010 (4) 1-0 } 17. c5 bxc5 18. Nb3 $14 ) 16. a3 Nf6 $11 ) ( 5. e3 Nf6 6. Bd3 d6 $11 { [%cal Ge6e5] folowed by ...e6-e5. } ) 5... Nf6 6. e3 d6 ( 6... b6 7. g3 Bb7 8. Bg2 O-O 9. O-O d6 10. a4 a5 11. Re1 Nbd7 $11 { Artemiev,V (2653) -Vallejo Pons,F (2711) Wch Blitz Doha 2016 (18) 1/2-1/2 } ) 7. Bd3 e5 8. dxe5 dxe5 9. e4 f4 { The structure favours Black, as long as White's pressure on e5 does not become threatening. } 10. Nc4 ( 10. Qe2 Bg4 11. O-O-O Nbd7 12. h3 Bxf3 $11 13. gxf3 $6 O-O-O $15 { Sahil,T (2016) -Van Dooren,D (2390) Dieren op 2016 (3) 1/2-1/2 } ) 10... Nc6 11. h3 O-O 12. O-O Bd7 13. Qd2 Rae8 14. b4 ( 14. Na5 $2 g5 $17 ( 14... b6 15. Nxc6 Bxc6 16. Rfe1 a5 17. Qc3 $16 { Arkell, K (2433) -Glek, I (2547) EU-ch Seniors 50 Blitz 2014 (8) 1-0 } ) 15. Bb5 Qg7 16. Bxc6 bxc6 $19 { [%csl Ge4] } ) ( 14. a4 g5 $17 15. Nxg5 $2 Qg7 $19 16. h4 Kh8 ) 14... b5 15. Nb2 Nxb4 $11 *
