1. d4 e6 2. Nf3 f5 3. Bg5 Be7 4. h4 { Maintaining the tension looks right in the short term, but creates a long time weakness. White will find it difficult to castle short. } 4... Nf6 5. Nc3 ( 5. e3 O-O 6. Bd3 b6 7. Nbd2 c5 8. c3 Nc6 9. Qe2 d5 $11 ) ( { I was expecting } 5. Nbd2 { examined in the next line. } ) 5... d5 ( { I did not like that much } 5... O-O 6. Bxf6 Bxf6 7. e4 d5 ( 7... fxe4 8. Nxe4 ) 8. exd5 ( 8. e5 Be7 9. Ne2 c5 10. c3 Qb6 ) 8... exd5 9. Qd2 { [%cal Ge1c1] followed by 0-0-0. } ) 6. e3 c5 7. Bd3 { After this natural move and Black's answer, White does not have a plan based on Ne2-f4. } ( { I mainly calculated } 7. Ne2 Qb6 8. Qc1 ( 8. Rb1 Nc6 $11 ) 8... Nc6 9. c3 Bd7 10. Nf4 O-O 11. Nd3 ( 11. Bd3 Rae8 { [%cal Gf6e4] followed by ...Ne4. } ) 11... Rae8 12. Nde5 Nxe5 13. Nxe5 Bb5 $11 ) 7... O-O 8. dxc5 Nbd7 9. Na4 ( { I expected } 9. b4 b6 ( 9... a5 10. a3 b6 11. Nd4 Ne5 12. Na4 $1 ) 10. Nd4 Ne5 $15 ) 9... Qa5+ 10. c3 b5 $1 11. cxb6 ( 11. b4 Qxa4 12. Qxa4 bxa4 $19 { does not yield White any compensation for the piece. } ) ( 11. c6 Nb8 12. b4 Qxa4 13. Qxa4 bxa4 14. b5 ( 14. Ne5 Bd6 $19 ) ( 14. Bb5 a5 $19 ) 14... a6 $19 ) 11... axb6 12. b3 $6 ( 12. Bc2 b5 13. b4 Qc7 14. Nc5 Nxc5 15. bxc5 Qxc5 $17 ) 12... b5 13. Nb2 Qxc3+ 14. Qd2 Bb4 15. Ke2 Qxd2+ ( 15... Ne4 $19 { is very strong, too, but I thought that Black may be hanging a bit later. The game continuation is simple and convincing. } ) 16. Nxd2 Bc3 17. Rhb1 b4 { White is paralysed. } 18. Nf3 Nc5 19. Bxf6 ( { I planned to meet } 19. Nd4 { with } 19... e5 { , calculating such lines: } 20. Nxf5 e4 ( 20... Nxd3 21. Ne7+ Kf7 22. Nxc8 Nxb2 $19 ) 21. Ne7+ Kf7 22. Nxc8 exd3+ 23. Nxd3 Nxd3 24. Kxd3 ( 24. Nd6+ Ke6 $19 ) 24... Rfxc8 $19 ) 19... Rxf6 20. Ne1 e5 21. Kd1 e4 22. Bb5 Ba6 23. Ba4 ( 23. Bxa6 Rfxa6 24. Kc2 Rxa2 25. Rxa2 Rxa2 $19 ) 23... f4 ( 23... Nd3 $19 { also wins, but why to exchange pieces so quickly? } ) 24. exf4 Rxf4 25. f3 Rxh4 26. Kc2 Rh2 27. Bc6 Rd8 28. Rd1 Nd3 29. Nbxd3 exd3+ 30. Kb1 d2 { Neef,M (2480) -Marin,M (2437) UKA Invitational Uhlmann 2023 (1.4) 0-1 } ( 30... d2 31. Nc2 Be2 32. Ne3 d4 $19 ) *
