1. d4 e6 2. Nf3 f5 3. Bg5 Be7 4. h4 Nf6 5. Nbd2 { Threatening e2-e4 without blocking the path of the c2-pawn. } 5... O-O ( 5... d5 { is also possible, but I thoguth that with the path clear for the c2-pawn, this would be less desirable. } ) 6. Bxf6 Bxf6 7. e4 c5 ( 7... d5 8. exd5 exd5 $11 { is a more passive version for White of the similar line with the knight on c3. } ) 8. dxc5 ( 8. e5 Be7 9. Bc4 ( 9. d5 d6 $5 10. Ng5 g6 ) 9... cxd4 10. Nxd4 Qb6 11. N4b3 { Winfridsson, O (2080) -Stone, A (2254) Coventry op 2005 (1) 0-1 } ( 11. c3 Nc6 ) 11... Qc7 12. Qe2 a6 13. a4 b6 $15 ) ( 8. c3 cxd4 9. cxd4 d5 $11 { Now that the pawn on d4 is a target, this is entirely wellcome. } ) 8... Bxb2 9. Rb1 Ba3 10. exf5 Bxc5 11. fxe6 d5 12. Bd3 Bxe6 13. Rxb7 Nd7 14. O-O ( 14. Ng5 $2 Bxf2+ ) 14... h6 { Black has great compensation for the pawn, due to his free development and the weakness on h4. } 15. c4 ( 15. Re1 Bg4 $11 ) ( 15. Rb3 Bb6 $11 { clearing the c5-square for the knight. } ) ( 15. Rb1 Nf6 16. c4 Ng4 17. Qe2 Qd6 18. cxd5 Bxd5 19. Bc4 Nxf2 20. Rxf2 Rae8 21. Qf1 Bxf2+ 22. Qxf2 Bxc4 23. Nxc4 Qd3 24. Rc1 Re2 25. Qf1 Qe4 26. Kh1 Rxa2 $11 ) 15... Bb6 16. Qe2 Bg4 17. Bb1 Qc8 18. Qd3 Qxb7 19. Qh7+ Kf7 $11 20. Bg6+ $2 Kf6 21. Bd3 Bxf3 22. Nxf3 Rae8 $19 *
