1. d4 e6 2. Nf3 f5 3. Bf4 Nf6 4. e3 Be7 5. Bd3 { WHite takes measures against ...Ne4, but exposes his bishop in the long run. } 5... O-O 6. O-O d6 7. c4 Nc6 ( 7... Ne4 { can now be met with } 8. Bxe4 fxe4 9. Nfd2 d5 10. Nc3 $14 Rxf4 $6 { is not justified with two knights on the board. } 11. exf4 Nc6 12. cxd5 exd5 13. Re1 Nxd4 ( 13... Bf6 14. Qb3 $18 ) 14. Nb3 Nxb3 15. Qxb3 c6 16. Rxe4 $18 ) 8. h3 { Even though ...Nh5 is not a threat, this is a useful move. The point is that after ...Nd7, White's minor pieces would be in danger, due to the bishop's presence on d3. } ( 8. Nc3 Nd7 $14 9. d5 { The most consistent answer. } ( { After } 9. Bg3 e5 { the threats...e5-e4 and ... f5-f4 force White to release the tension. } 10. dxe5 dxe5 11. Nd5 Bd6 12. Bc2 a5 $11 ) 9... Nce5 { We see another way of taking advantage of the bishop's exposure. } ( 9... Nb4 { is playable, but may yield WHite some small advantage. } 10. dxe6 Nc5 11. Bb1 Bxe6 12. a3 Nc6 13. Nd5 $14 ) 10. Nd4 ( 10. dxe6 Nxf3+ $1 11. Qxf3 Nc5 12. Bc2 a5 $11 ) 10... Nc5 11. Be2 g5 12. b4 $1 { The best chance. } ( 12. Bxg5 Bxg5 13. f4 Bh6 14. b4 exd5 15. cxd5 Ne4 16. Nxe4 fxe4 17. fxe5 Rxf1+ 18. Bxf1 Bxe3+ 19. Kh1 dxe5 $13 ) ( 12. Bxe5 dxe5 $11 ) 12... gxf4 13. bxc5 dxc5 14. Nxe6 Bxe6 15. exf4 ( 15. dxe6 fxe3 $11 ) 15... Ng6 16. dxe6 Nxf4 17. Bf3 c6 18. Rb1 Rb8 { The position has calmed down. The pawn on e6 is not too threatening and is likely to fall in the long run. Black's structure is by no means worse. In fact, he has the d4-square and the whole long diagonal, while the bishop on f3 is passive. } 19. Re1 Bf6 20. g3 Qxd1 21. Nxd1 Ng6 22. Rb3 Ne7 23. Ne3 Bd4 $11 ) 8... Nd7 $14 9. Bh2 e5 { White has the time to save his minor pieces, but his queenside is underdeveloped still. } 10. Bc2 ( 10. Be2 Bf6 11. Nc3 exd4 12. exd4 ( 12. Nxd4 Nc5 $11 ) 12... g5 13. Nd5 Bg7 $13 14. Nxg5 Qxg5 15. Nxc7 f4 $5 16. Nxa8 Nxd4 17. Kh1 Qd8 18. Bf3 Nc5 $44 ) 10... e4 11. Nfd2 Nb4 12. Ba4 { This bishop had to move a lot. } 12... c5 { Starting to question White's central space advantage. } 13. Nc3 ( { With the development incomplete, } 13. a3 { can be met with } 13... Nd3 14. Bc2 Nxb2 15. Qe2 cxd4 16. exd4 Nb6 $13 ) 13... Kh8 ( 13... cxd4 14. exd4 Kh8 { is another possible move order. } ) 14. a3 ( 14. dxc5 Nxc5 $15 ) 14... cxd4 ( 14... Nd3 15. Bc2 Nxb2 16. Qb1 $16 { Now is when White's better development than in the similar line above tells. } ) 15. axb4 ( 15. exd4 Nc6 $11 { White's centre is under pressure and Black's kingside majority should not be underestimated. } ) 15... dxc3 16. bxc3 Nb6 17. Bb3 Qe8 $11 { [%cal Gc8e6,Ge8c6] Planning to attack c4 with ...Be6 and ...Qc6. } 18. f3 $5 { This does not change Black's plans. } 18... Be6 19. fxe4 fxe4 20. Rxf8+ Bxf8 21. Qb1 Bg8 $11 *
